cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with object detection in autonomous vehicles using deep neural networks and lidar sensors. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with autonomous vehicles, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper proposes a new approach for cooperative object detection, which involves sharing features between vehicles, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper proposes a computationally efficient approach, which involves balancing computation and communication load, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
